          @BarcaPlsLetMeDown - This is exactly why you don't rotate all the key players in the same matches. You rest them one by one. Then the rest of the team's chemistry stays the same and the incoming player only has to adapt themselves into the existing structure. But if you rest everybody for one match, then the ones who aren't in form (Coutinho, Malcom, Vidal, Umtiti) have to invent a title-winning team. And they can't, that's why they aren't generally starters this season in the first place.
